description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Therapy Support Worker to join the Adult Speech and Language Therapy Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work along-side the therapists, supporting the team with general administration but also working with patients with swallowing, eating and drinking difficulties. This involves observing patients and feeding back to the therapists and demonstrating best practice in supporting individuals to eat and drink. It also involves some teaching to staff on the wards at Stoke Mandeville Hospital and in local care homes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who is enthusiastic and caring and has experience with supporting patients to eat and drink, informal training will be provided; this is an opportunity to develop skills and knowledge in this specific field of caring.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some of our work is carried out in local care homes in Aylesbury so the post holder would need to be able to travel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a friendly, supportive and dynamic team with supervision, appraisal, CPD and in-service training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Stangroom, Speech and Language Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address : sarah.stangroom1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number : 01296 315247&lt;/p&gt;
